(firstQuint)Follow up by General Practitioner After Self-poisoning.

 Patients hospitalized after an episode of self poisoning will be randomly assigned into intervention an control groups.

 The intervention is close follow up by general practitioner six months.

 Both groups will receive treatment as usual.

.

 Follow up by General Practitioner After Self-poisoning@highlight

The study hypothesis is that follow up from general practitioner after hospitalization for self poisoning will decrease suicidal behaviour.

